1.  RightSize.java presents menu. User choose the desired sample type in menu and action listener creates appropriate document.
 
2. SRSDocument (for example) presents SRS Panel which gathers user input and returns control to the document that created it when calling
function returns.    

3. SRSDocument calculations function collects user input by calling panel getters. then it does calculations.

4. SRSDocument calculations method then calls view.update which takes the results as arguments and then shows them to user.

